Vasily Chuikov was born in the village of Krasnaya Polyana, in the Tula Governorate of the Russian Empire (now in the Tula Oblast of Russia). He was the son of a peasant. input: Write a short biography of R. Selvaraj (politician).
output:
R. Selvaraj (politician)

## Early life

R. Selvaraj was born in 1950 in the village of Kallupatti in the Theni district of Tamil Nadu. He completed his schooling in the village and then moved to Madurai to pursue higher education. He completed his Bachelor of Arts degree from the Madurai Kamaraj University and then went on to complete his Master of Arts degree from the same university.

## Political career

R. Selvaraj started his political career in the 1980s when he joined the Indian National Congress party. He quickly rose through the ranks and was elected as the president of the party's youth wing in the Madurai district. In 1989, he was elected to the Tamil Nadu Legislative Assembly as a member of the Indian National Congress party. He served as a member of the assembly for two terms, from 1989 to 1996 and from 1996 to 2001.

In 2001, R. Selvaraj left the Indian National Congress party and joined the Dravida Munnet

Xi Jinping attended elementary school in Beijing and middle school in Yan'an, Shaanxi. He then attended the prestigious Peking University, where he studied Chinese literature. input: Write a short biography of Timothy Evans.
output:
Timothy Evans was born in 1864. He was a carpenter by trade. He married Catherine Eddowes, a widow, in 1886. They had a son, John, born in 1888.

Evans was a quiet, unassuming man. He was a devout Christian and a member of the Church of England. He was also a member of the Salvation Army.

Evans and his family lived in a small house in the East End of London. They were poor but they were happy.

In 1888, Evans's wife, Catherine, was murdered. The police arrested Evans and charged him with her murder.

Evans was tried and convicted of the murder. He was sentenced to death.

On the day of his execution, Evans made a statement to the press. He said that he was innocent and that he had been framed by the police.

Evans was hanged on November 9, 1888.

input: Write a short biography of Gopi Sundar.
output:
Gopi Sundar is an Indian music composer and singer. He is known for his work in Telugu, Tamil, Kannada, Malayalam and Hindi films. He has won two Filmfare Awards South and two SIIMA Awards.

## Early life

Gopi Sundar was born in a Telugu family in Hyderabad, Telangana. He is the son of music director S. V. Krishna Reddy. He completed his schooling at St. Ann's High School, Secunderabad. He completed his graduation in B.Tech from Jawaharlal Nehru Technological University, Hyderabad.

## Career

Gopi Sundar started his career as a music director in 2005 with the Telugu film Nuvvostanante Nenoddantana. He has composed music for more than 50 films in Telugu, Tamil, Kannada, Malayalam and Hindi. He has won two Filmfare Awards South and two SIIMA Awards.
